<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Achyrachaena</i> <i>mollis</i> and/or <i>Layia</i> <i>fremontii</i> are characteristically present in the herbaceous layer with <i>Blennosperma</i> <i>nanum</i>, <i>Brodiaea</i> <i>minor</i>, <i>Centromadia</i> <i>fitchii</i>, <i>Chlorogalum</i> <i>angustifolium</i>, <i>Cicendia</i> <i>quadrangularis</i>, <i>Clarkia</i> <i>purpurea</i>, <i>Dodecatheon</i> <i>clevelandii</i> ssp. <i>patulum</i>, <i>Downingia</i> <i>cuspidata</i>, <i>Downingia</i> <i>ornatissima</i>, <i>Lasthenia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Lasthenia</i> <i>fremontii</i>, <i>Lepidium</i> <i>nitidum</i>, <i>Leptosiphon</i> <i>parviflorus</i>, <i>Limnanthes</i> <i>douglasii</i> ssp. <i>rosea</i>, <i>Microseris</i> <i>acuminata</i>, <i>Navarretia</i> <i>tagetina</i>, <i>Plagiobothrys</i> <i>austiniae</i>, <i>Plagiobothrys</i> <i>greenei</i>, <i>Plantago</i> <i>erecta</i>, <i>Taeniatherum</i> <i>caput</i>-<i>medusae</i>, <i>Trifolium</i> <i>depauperatum</i>, <i>Triphysaria</i> <i>eriantha</i> ssp. <i>eriantha</i>, <i>Vulpia</i> <i>microstachys</i> and <i>Zigadenus</i> <i>fremontii</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 50 cm; cover is intermittent to continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Achyrachaena mollis, Clarkia purpurea, Layia fremontii, Taeniatherum caput-medusae</i>, and/or <i>Triphysaria eriantha</i> ssp. <i>eriantha</i> are present as diagnostic species in the herbaceous layer; other diagnostic vernal pool species may be present such as <i>Lasthenia fremontii</i>(Barbour et al. 2007).</li>
		
		<li><i>Zigadenus fremontii</i> is characteristic in the herbaceous layer with non-native species such as <i>Lolium perenne</i> and <i>Achyrachaena mollis.</i></li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Short-inundated, shallow, flashy vernal hardpan pools; mesic meadows with subsurface waterflow in winter and early spring. Soils are shallow and rocky. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Achyrachaena mollis</i> as a FAC* plant. </div>
</div>

        
