    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Great Valley</b> (262Aa-b). Stands of the <i>Layia fremontii-Achyrachaena mollis</i> association occur in the northern Sacramento Valley (Barbour et al. 2007b, Klein et al. 2007). Stands of the <i>Plagiobothrys austiniae-Achyrachaena mollis</i> association occur in volcanic rock vernal pools in the northeastern Sacramento Valley (Barbour et al. 2007b).</li>
        
            <li><b>Sierra Nevada Foothills</b> (M261Fa-b). Stands with <i>Plagiobothrys greenei</i> occur in the central Sacramento Valley, such as the Deer Creek Hills area of Sacramento Co., whereas stands with <i>Achyraechaena mollis</i> and <i>Plagiobothrys austiniae</i> occur in the northern Sacramento Valley on Tuscan flows of Butte and Tehama Cos. (Klein et al. 2007).</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> Threats are primarily from loss of habitat due to conversion to agriculture and development. Short inundation leads to a higher number of non-natives, especially <i>Hordeum marinum, Lolium perenne, </i>and <i>Taeniatherum caput-medusae, </i>as compared to the <i>Lasthenia glaberrima </i>and <i>Lasthenia fremontii-Downingia </i>(<i>bicornuta</i>) alliances. </div>
</div>

    

    

